t\":{\"content\":\"# AR-021 Delta Specification: CLI build 命令\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nImplement the `build` command for the AgentCube CLI to build container images from packaged agent workspaces, supporting local Docker builds and cloud provider builds with proxy support, version management, and comprehensive error handling.\\n\\n## Requirements\\n\\n### Requirement: Build command registration and default options\\n\\nThe system SHALL provide a `build` command that builds container images from packaged agent workspaces with configurable options.\\n\\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\\n- Command name: `build`\\n- Supports workspace path specification\\n- Supports proxy configuration for dependency resolution\\n- Supports cloud provider selection\\n- Supports custom output path for build artifacts\\n- Provides verbose mode for detailed logging\\n\\n**Scenarios:**\\n\\n#### Scenario 1.1: Command registration and default options\\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube CLI Typer application is initialized\\n- **WHEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube build` without options\\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use these defaults:\\n  - `workspace`: `\\\".\\\"` (current directory)\\n  - `proxy`: `None`\\n  - `cloud_provider`: `None`\\n  - `output`: `None`\\n  - `verbose`: `False`\\n\\n#### Scenario 1.2: Command option validation\\n- **GIVEN** the user provides CLI options\\n- **WHEN** options include `--workspace`, `--proxy`, `--cloud-provider`, `--output`, `--verbose`\\n- **THEN** the system SHALL accept all valid option values:\\n  - `workspace`: string path to workspace directory\\n  - `proxy`: string URL or None\\n  - `cloud_provider`: string provider name or None\\n  - `output`: string path or None\\n  - `...\n  Line 39: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775866334951,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286214b10ffeHQQzCVYar8lUNg\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79e1c7b2001HhVporNgxaxq2a\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79e1b078001T2EUzSeq0BQ2gB\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286214b10ffeHQQzCVYar8lUNg\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Create